  "text": "## Grafana Unified Alerting Rule Evaluation and Notification Flow\n\n### Overview\nGrafana's unified alerting system (ngalert) evaluates alert rules on a schedule and dispatches fired alerts through notification receivers. The flow consists of four main components: rule scheduling, rule evaluation, state management, and notification dispatch.\n\n### Rule Scheduler\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go`\n\nThe scheduler is the entry point that orchestrates periodic evaluation of alert rules. Key functions:\n- `Run(ctx context.Context)`: Starts the scheduler, initializes a ticker, and enters the main evaluation loop\n- `schedulePeriodic(ctx context.Context, t *ticker.T)`: Main loop that:\n  - Tracks which alert rules are scheduled for evaluation\n  - Fetches alert rules from the rules store periodically\n  - Sends evaluation signals to individual alert rule routines\n  - Handles rule additions, deletions, and updates\n  - Uses retry configuration for resilience\n\nThe scheduler maintains a rule registry where each alert rule has its own dedicated goroutine for execution.\n\n### Alert Rule Evaluation\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go`\n\nEach alert rule runs in its own goroutine orchestrated by the `alertRule` struct. Key functions:\n\n- `newAlertRule()`: Factory function that creates an alert rule with state manager, evaluator factory, and sender dependencies\n\n- `Run()`: Main loop for an individual alert rule that:\n  - Receives evaluation signals via a channel (`evalCh`)\n  - Receives update signals to change rule configuration (`updateCh`)\n  - Handles rule state resets when updated or paused\n  - Implements exponential backoff retry logic\n  - Delegates to `evaluate()` for actual evaluation\n\n- `Eval(eval *Evaluation)`: Signals the rule to perform evaluation by sending to `evalCh`\n\n- `evaluate(ctx, e *Evaluation, span, shouldRetry, logger)`: Core evaluation logic that:\n  - Creates a new evaluator from the factory for the rule's condition\n  - Calls `ruleEval.Evaluate()` to execute queries/expressions\n  - Measures evaluation duration and tracks metrics\n  - Calls `stateManager.ProcessEvalResults()` with evaluation results and a callback to send alerts\n  - Implements retry logic with exponential backoff\n\n- `send(ctx, logger, states StateTransitions)`: Converts state transitions to PostableAlerts and calls `sender.Send()`\n\n- `expireAndSend(ctx, states)`: Sends resolved alerts when rules are deleted or updated\n\n### Evaluation Engine\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/eval/eval.go`\n\nThe evaluator executes the rule's query/expression condition. Key components:\n\n- `EvaluatorFactory`: Interface with `Create()` method that builds evaluators for rule conditions\n\n- `NewEvaluatorFactory()`: Creates the evaluator factory, configured with evaluation timeout and result limits\n\n- `ConditionEvaluator`: Interface with:\n  - `Evaluate(ctx, now time.Time)`: Evaluates condition and returns typed Results\n  - `EvaluateRaw(ctx, now time.Time)`: Returns raw backend response\n\n- `EvaluateAlert()`: Converts backend query response to alert instance states (determined by alert values, thresholds, and evaluation time)\n\n### State Management and Transitions\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/state/manager.go`\n\nManages alert instance state and determines which alerts to send to notification receivers:\n\n- `Manager`: Core state management component that:\n  - Caches alert instance states per rule\n  - Persists state to database\n  - Coordinates with historian for audit trail\n\n- `ProcessEvalResults(ctx, evaluatedAt time.Time, alertRule, results, extraLabels, send Sender)`: Main method that:\n  - Calls `setNextStateForRule()` to compute state transitions based on evaluation results\n  - Handles NoData and Error states based on rule configuration\n  - Processes missing series (firing alerts with no data in current evaluation)\n  - Calls `updateLastSentAt()` to determine which states should be sent\n  - Persists all state changes (both sent and unsent)\n  - Records state transitions in historian\n  - Invokes the `send` callback with state transitions to send\n\n- `setNextStateForRule()`: Determines new states for each alert instance based on:\n  - Evaluation results and thresholds\n  - Previous state of the alert instance\n  - Pending duration (time alert must breach threshold before firing)\n  - NoDataState and ExecutionErrorState rule configuration\n\n- `updateLastSentAt()`: Filters state transitions to identify which should be sent based on:\n  - State changes (e.g., firing to normal)\n  - Resend delay (30 seconds by default)\n  - Resolved alert retention period\n\n- `DeleteStateByRuleUID()`: Removes all instances of a rule and creates resolved state transitions for firing alerts\n\n### Alert Notification Dispatch\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/sender/router.go`\n\nRoutes alerts to internal and/or external Alertmanagers:\n\n- `AlertsRouter`: Handles alert routing based on organization configuration. Key functions:\n  - `NewAlertsRouter()`: Creates router with dependencies on multi-org alertmanager and external alertmanager configuration\n  - `Send(ctx, key AlertRuleKey, alerts PostableAlerts)`: Main dispatch function that:\n    - Checks if organization is configured for internal, external, or both alertmanagers\n    - Gets org's alertmanager from `multiOrgNotifier.AlertmanagerFor()`\n    - Calls `PutAlerts()` on the alertmanager\n    - Sends to external alertmanagers if configured via `ExternalAlertmanager.SendAlerts()`\n    - Broadcasts alerts to cluster peers if enabled\n  - `SyncAndApplyConfigFromDatabase()`: Periodically syncs alertmanager configuration from database\n  - Maintains list of external alertmanagers per organization\n\n### Multi-Org Alertmanager\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/multiorg_alertmanager.go`\n\nManages separate Alertmanager instances per Grafana organization:\n\n- `MultiOrgAlertmanager`: Container for organization-specific alertmanagers. Key functions:\n  - `NewMultiOrgAlertmanager()`: Factory that:\n    - Sets up clustering if configured (Redis for HA)\n    - Initializes per-org alertmanager factory\n    - Configures alert broadcast channel for cluster communication\n  - `AlertmanagerFor(orgID)`: Returns or creates alertmanager for given organization\n  - Creates per-org Alertmanager instances on demand with isolation\n\n### Internal Alertmanager (Per-Organization)\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/alertmanager.go`\n\nHandles notification delivery and routing for a single organization:\n\n- `alertmanager`: Wraps the core `GrafanaAlertmanager` from the alerting library. Key functions:\n  - `NewAlertmanager()`: Creates org-specific alertmanager that:\n    - Initializes state stores for silences and notification logs\n    - Sets up maintenance options for periodic garbage collection\n    - Loads persisted silence and notification log state\n    - Configures dispatch timer (async or sync)\n  - `PutAlerts(ctx, postableAlerts)`: Receives alerts and:\n    - Converts Grafana alert models to alerting library models\n    - Calls `Base.PutAlerts()` on the wrapped `GrafanaAlertmanager`\n    - This sends alerts through the Alertmanager's dispatch pipeline to receivers/integrations\n\n### Service Integration\n**File:** `pkg/services/ngalert/ngalert.go`\n\nWires up all components:\n- Creates and initializes the scheduler\n- Creates state manager with persistence layer\n- Creates evaluator factory\n- Creates alerts router\n- Creates multi-org alertmanager\n- Coordinates lifecycle of all services\n\n### Complete Call Chain\n\n1. **Scheduler Start**: `schedule.Run()` → `schedulePeriodic()`\n2. **Rule Evaluation Signal**: Scheduler sends eval signal to alert rule's channel\n3. **Rule Processing**: `alertRule.Run()` receives signal → calls `Eval()`\n4. **Evaluation Execution**: `evaluate()` → `evalFactory.Create()` → `ConditionEvaluator.Evaluate()` → `EvaluateAlert()`\n5. **State Processing**: `stateManager.ProcessEvalResults()` → `setNextStateForRule()` → `updateLastSentAt()`\n6. **Alert Dispatch**: Callback invokes `alertRule.send()` → `AlertsRouter.Send()`\n7. **Routing to Alertmanager**: `AlertsRouter.Send()` → `MultiOrgAlertmanager.AlertmanagerFor()` → org's `Alertmanager.PutAlerts()`\n8. **Notification Delivery**: `Alertmanager.PutAlerts()` → `GrafanaAlertmanager.PutAlerts()` → dispatcher sends to receivers/integrations\n\nThis modular architecture allows for:\n- Per-organization isolation via MultiOrgAlertmanager\n- Flexible routing (internal/external alertmanagers)\n- Proper state tracking and notification deduplication\n- Resilience with retry logic and state persistence\n- Clustering support for high availability"
}

